dialog: We're safe, my lady.Thank you.
He's......dead.He took a little tumble off the cliff.
Mama!
Come.
At last! Helm's DeepThere it is, Helm's Deep.We're safe!
Eothain!Freda!
Where is the rest?
This is all we could save, my lady.
Take it to the caves.

Simbelmyne. Ever has it grown on the tombs of my forebearers. Now it shall cover the grave of my son. Alas that these evil days should be mine. The young perish and the old linger. That I should live......to see the last days of my house.
Theodred's death was not of your making.
No parent should have to bury their child.
He was strong in life. His spirit will find its way to the halls of your fathers. Westu h'l. Fer'u, Th'odred, Fer'u.
They had no warning. They were unarmed. Now the Wild Men are moving through the Westfold, burning as they go. Rick, cot and tree.
Pull back! Pull back!

Sons of Gondor, of Rohan, my brothers. (They listen to him.) I see it in your eyes, the same fear that would take the heart of me. A day may come when the courage of men fails, when we forsake our friends and break all bonds of fellowship, but it is not this day! An hour of wolves and shattered shields when the age of men comes crashing down, but it is not this day! This day we fight!
By all that you hold dear on this good earth, I bid you stand! Men of the West!
It's gone Mr Frodo. The light's passed on, away towards the North. Something's drawn its gaze.
Where is Mama?
Hold your ground! Hold your ground!
Never thought I'd die fighting side by side with an elf.

The veiling shadow that glowers in the east takes shape.Sauron will suffer no rival.From the summit of Barad-durhis Eye watches ceaselessly.But he is not so mighty yetthat he is above fear.Doubt ever gnaws at him.The rumor has reached him.The heir of Numenor still lives.
This, in turn, has given riseto the belief......that there are no Dwarf women......and that Dwarves just spring outof holes in the ground...
...which is, of course, ridiculous.
It's the beards.
It's all right. Nobody panic.That was deliberate.It was deliberate.
I haven't seen my niece smilefor a long time.She was a girl when they broughther father back dead.Cut down by Orcs.She watched her mothersuccumb to grief.
Then she was left aloneto tend her king in growing fear.Doomed to wait upon an old manwho should have loved her as a father.
Make way for the king.Make way for Theoden.Make way for the king.
Our people are safe.We have paid for it with many lives.
So few. So few of you have returned.
My lady.
Gimli.?
Lord Aragorn......where is he?
No, I couldn'tI really couldn't.
What of those who cannot fight, my lord?The women and children?
He fell.
Draw all our forces behind the wall.Bar the gate.And set a watch on the surround.
Helm's Deep has one weakness.Its outer wall is solid rock......but for a small culvertat its base...... which is little more than a drain.
How? How can fire undo stone?
Get them into the caves. Saruman's arm will have grown long indeed if he thinks he can reach us here.
Sssh

This is but a taste of the terror that Saruman will unleash. All the more potent for he is driven now by fear of Sauron. Ride out and meet him head on. Draw him away from your women and children. You must fight.
They will be 300 leagues from here by now. Eomer cannot help us. I know what it is you want of me......but I will not bring further death to my people. I will not risk open war.
You have 2000 good men riding north as we speak. Eomer is loyal to you. His men will return and fight for their king.
By order of the king......the city must empty. We make for the refuge of Helm's Deep.
Do not burden yourself with treasures. Take only what provisions you need.
Open war is upon you, whether you would risk it or not.
Helm's Deep.
They flee to the mountains when they should stand and fight. Who will defend them if not their king?
He's only doing what he thinks is best for his people. Helm's Deep has saved them in the past.

There is no way out of that ravine. Theoden is walking into a trap. He thinks he's leading them to safety. What they will get is a massacre. Theoden has a strong will, but I fear for him. I fear for the survival of Rohan. He will need you before the end, Aragorn. The people of Rohan will need you. The defenses, to hold.
When last I looked......Theoden, not Aragorn, was King of Rohan.
What about side by side with a friend?,

Do you remember the Shire Mr Frodo? It will be Spring soon and the orchards will be in blossom. And the birds will be nesting in the hazel thickets. (He is crying.) And they will be sowing the summer barley in the lower fields, (Frodo opens his eyes and looks at him.) and eating the first of the strawberries and cream. Do you remember the taste of strawberries?

No Sam. I can't recall the taste of food, nor the sound of water or the touch of grass. I'm naked in the dark. There's' there's nothing, no veil between me and the wheel of fire. I can see him with my waking eyes!
Then let us be rid of it once and for all! Come on Mr Frodo, I can't carry it for you, but I can carry you! Come on!
Aragorn! Elessar!
For Frodo.
Look Mr Frodo, a doorway! We're almost there!
Aye! I could do that.
Clever Hobbits to climb so high!Mustn't go that way. Mustn't hurt the precious!

Sauron fears you, Aragorn.He fears what you may become.And so he'll strike hard and fastat the world of Men.He will use his puppet Sarumanto destroy Rohan.War is coming.Rohan must defend itselfand therein lies our first challenge......for Rohan is weak and ready to fall. The king's mind is enslavedit's an old device of Saruman's.His hold over King Theodenis now very strong.Sauron and Sarumanare tightening the noose.But for all their cunning......we have one advantage. The Ring remains hidden.And that we should seek to destroy it......has not yet enteredtheir darkest dreams. And so the weapon of the enemyis moving towards Mordor......in the hands of a Hobbit.Each day brings it closerto the fires of Mount Doom. We must trust now in Frodo.Everything depends upon speed......and the secrecy of his quest.
Did he?Did he, indeed? Good. Yes, very good.
The Black Gate of Mordor.
Oh, save us.My old Gaffer would have a thing or twoto say if he could see us now.
Master says to show himthe way into Mordor.So good Smeagol doesmaster says so.
I did.
That's it, then.We can't get past that.
Do not regret your decision to leave him.Frodo must finish this task alone.
You swore! You swore on the precious!
He's not alone.Sam went with him.
Thank you. It's good.
Sam, no!
Look!The gate.It's opening!I can see a way down.
I made some stew.It isn't much, but it's hot.
Really?
My uncle told me a strange thing.He said that you rode to warwith Thengel, my grandfather.But he must be mistaken.
King Theoden has a good memory.He was only a small child at the time.
Then you must be at least 60.
Seventy?But you cannot be 80!
I'm sorry. Please, eat.
Did we lose him? I think we lost him.
I'm going to rip outyour filthy little innards!
Come here!
Trees. Climb a tree.
What kind of devicecould bring down the wall?
You are one of the Dunedain.A descendant of Numenorblessed with long life.It was said that your racehad passed into legend.
There are few of us left.The Northern Kingdomwas destroyed long ago.
Eighty-seven.
If the wall is breachedHelm's Deep will fall.
Even if it is breached, it would takea number beyond reckoning......thousands, to storm the Keep.
Tens of thousands.
But, my lord, there is no such force.
A new power is rising.Its victory is at hand.
There will be no dawn for Men.
This night......the land will be stainedwith the blood of Rohan!March to Helm's Deep!Leave none alive!
Look. There's smoke to the south.
There was a time......when Saruman would walk in my woods.But now he has a mind of metal......and wheels.He no longer cares for growing things.
Isengard?
There is always smoke rising......from lsengard these days.
The eagles! The eagles are coming!
To war!
Frodo!
I'm here Sam!
What is it?
Destroy it!
The Ring is mine!
What are you waiting for? Just let it go!
Nooooooo!
They will hold.
Yeees! Yeees! Precious! My Precious!

The Grey Pilgrim. That's what they used to call me. Three hundred lives of Men I've walked this earth, and now I have no time. With luck, my search will not be in vain. Look to my coming at first light on the fifth day. At dawn, look to the east.
Go.
Go on! Now! Throw it in the fire!
No!
That horse is half mad, my lord. There's nothing you can do. Leave him.
F'ste, stille n', f'ste, stille n'. Lac is drefed, gefr'gon.
Hw't nemna' 'e? Hm? Hw't nemna' 'e? (
His name is Brego. He was my cousin's horse.
Brego. 'in nama is cynglic.
Man le trasta, Brego? Man cenich?
Fifteen, sixteen.
I was raised in Rivendell......for a time.Turn this fellow free. He's seen enough of war.
Legolas!
Thirty three, thirty four.
I have heard of the magic of Elves......but I did not look for it in a Ranger from the North.You speak as one of their own.
Merry!
No, no. I'm going to save you.
Come on then, come on!
You already did. Eowyn, my body is broken. You have to let me go.
Smeagol promised!
Smeagol lied!
AAAAAAAAAhhhhhhhhhh!
AAAAAHH
That still only counts as one!
I know your face, Eowyn. My eyes darken.
Frodo!
Master!
Now!
I know, Mr. Frodo.I doubt even these Elvish cloakswill hide us in there.
No!No! No, master!They catch you! They catch you!Don't take it to him.He wants the precious.Always he is looking for it.And the precious is wantingto go back to him.But we mustn't let him have it.
No! There's another way.More secret. A dark way.
Why haven't you spoken of this before?
Because master did not ask.
He's up to something.
Are you saying there's another wayinto Mordor?
I do not ask you to come with me, Sam.
Yes. There's a path......and some stairs.And then......a tunnel.
He's led us this far, Sam.
Mr. Frodo, no.
He's been true to his word.
I knew you'd find me.
Merry!
No.
Yes.
Are you going to leave me?
No Merry, I'm going to look after you.
Their pace has quickened.They must have caught our scent.Hurry!
Hands off! That shiny shirt, that's mine!
Merry! Merry it's me. It's Pippin!
Come on, Gimli!
Less than a day ahead of us. Come.
Come, Gimli! We're gaining on them!
I'm wasted on cross-country.We Dwarves are natural sprinters.Very dangerous over short distances.
He's gone.
Merry!
Hooom!
Three days and nights pursuit.No food. No rest.And no sign of our quarrybut what bare rock can tell.
Not idly do the leaves of Lorien fall.
Run, Merry!
They may yet be alive.
Little Orcs.
It's talking, Merry.The tree is talking.
Tree?I am no tree!I am an Ent.
Let's put a maggot hole in your belly!
Treebeard, some call me.
And whose side are you on?
Aaagh!
A tree-herder.A shepherd of the forest.
Side?I am on nobody's side......because nobody's on my sidelittle Orc.Nobody cares for the woods anymore.
We're not Orcs! We're Hobbits!
Gandalf!
You shall not pass!
No! No!
I am a servant of the Secret Fire, wielder of the flame of Anor. Go back to the Shadow.The dark fire will not avail you,flame of Udun!
Don't talk to it, Merry.Don't encourage it!
You cannot pass!
Gandalf!
It's Saruman's army.The war has started.
Give me your hand.
Frodo.
It's gone. It's done.
Yes Mr Frodo. It's over now.
I can see the Shire. The Brandywine River. Bag End. Gandalf's fireworks. The lights on the party tree.
Rosie Cotton dancing. She had ribbons in her hair. If ever I was to marry someone, it would have been her. It would've been her.
I'm glad to be with you Samwise Gamgee here at the end of all things. They hug.
Take my hand.
No! Don't you let go! Don't let go! Reeeaaach!
Frodo!Frodo!
Gondor is lost. There is no hope for men. Why do the fools fly? Better to die sooner than late. For die we must.
No tomb for Denethor and Faramir. No long slow sleep of death embalmed. We shall burn like the heathen Kings of old. Bring wood and oil.
I am steward of the house of An'rion. Thus have I walked, and thus now I will sleep.
Let him go, you filth! Let him go!
You will not touch him again! Come on then, finish it!
Keep breathing. That's the key.Breathe.
They've run as if the very whipsof their masters were behind them.
You are soldiers of Gondor. No matter what comes through that gate you will stand your ground.
Steady! Steady!
We're not going no further......until we've had a breather.
Get a fire going!
Volley! Fire!
I think we might have made a mistakeleaving the Shire, Pippin.
Merry!Merry!
What's making that noise?
It's the trees.
Peregrin Took my lad, there is a task now to be done. Another opportunity for one of the Shire folk to prove their great worth. You must not fail me.
It's been very quiet across the river.
The Orcs are lying low. The garrison may have moved out. We've sent scouts to Cair Andros. If the Orcs attack from the North, we'll have some warning.
No.
We need 10 more.
Quiet.
Bad idea! Very handy in a tight spot these lads, despite the fact they're dead.
You gave us your word!
I hold your oath fulfilled. Go. Be at peace.
Merry!
Nooooo!
Nooooooo! Noooooo!
Eowyn.
Release us!
Hello?Treebeard?Where has he gone?
Good Smeagol always helps.
Did you hear that?There it is again.Something's not right here.Not right at all.
I had the loveliest dream last night.There was this large barrelfull of pipe-weed.And we smoked all of it.And then......you were sick.I'd give anything for a whiff of Old Toby.
You just said something...Treeish.
I go to my fathers, in whose mighty company; I shall not now feel ashamed.
Lead the way, Smeagol.
You!
Than what?
Than me!
I've always been taller than you.
Pippin, everyone knows I'm the tall one.You're the short one.
Please, Merry.You're what? Three-foot-six? At the most?Whereas me, I'm pushing 3'7". 3'8"!
You're taller.
Who?
I don't take orders from stinking Morgul-rats!
You touch it and I'll stick this blade in your gut!
The scum tried to knife me. Kill him!
That's for Frodo!
It's going to the Great Eye, along with everything else.
No, I didn't. I was just stretching.
And the Shire!
Stop your squealing you dunghill rat!
I'm gonna bleed you like a stuck pig!
Not if I stick you first!
Sam!
Oh Sam, I'm so sorry. Sorry for everything.
Let's get you out of here.
Rohan.Home of the Horse-lords.There's something strange at work here.Some evil gives speedto these creatures.Sets its will against us.
And that's for my old gaffer!
Legolas! What do your Elf-eyes see?
The Uruks turn northeast.They are taking the Hobbits to lsengard.

The Old World will burnin the fires of industry.The forests will fall.A new order will rise.We will drive the machine of warwith the sword and the spear...... and the iron fists of the Orc. We have only to remove those who oppose us.
I want them armed and ready to marchwithin two weeks!
But, my lord, there are too many!They cannot all be armed in timewe don't have the means.
Build a dam, block the streamwork the furnaces night and day.
We don't have enough fuelto feed the fires.
Hobbits?Never heard of a Hobbit before.Sounds like Orc mischief to me!They come with fire.They come with axes.Gnawing, biting, breakinghacking, burning! Destroyers and usurpers! Curse them!
The world is changing.Who now has the strength to standagainst the armies of Isengard......and Mordor?To stand against the might of Sauronand Saruman......and the union of the two towers?
Together, my Lord Sauron...... we shall rule this Middle-earth.
Saruman.
Maybe you are......and maybe you aren't.The White Wizard will know.
See? See?We've led you out.Hurry, Hobbitses. Hurry! Very lucky we find you. Nice Hobbit.
It's a bog. He's led us into a swamp.
No!You don't understand. We're Hobbits!Halflings!Shire-folk!
Saruman.
The White Wizard?
Here.

A swamp, yes, yes.Come, master. We will take youon safe paths through the mist.Come, Hobbits! Come! We go quickly. I found it. I did.The way through the marshes.Orcs don't use it.Orcs don't know it.They go around for miles and miles.Come quickly.Soft and quick as shadows we must be.
No, no birdses to eat.No crunchable birdses.We are famished! Yes!Famished we are, precious!
I hate this place. It's too quiet.There's been no sight nor soundof a bird for two days.
Well, starve, then. And good riddance!
Fly, you fools!
What does it eats?Is it tasty?,It tries to chokes us!We can't eats Hobbit food!We must starve!
Gandalf!
What is it, Mr. Frodo?
Oh, cruel Hobbit.It does not care if we be hungry.Does not care if we should die. Not like master.Master cares.Master knows.Yes.Precious.Once it takes hold of us......it never lets go.
Don't touch me!
Nothing.Just a dream.
Can you see the bottom?
No!Gandalf!
No! Don't look down, Sam!Just keep going!
Bogs and ropeand goodness knows what.It's not natural. None of it.
What's in this?
Nothing.Just a bit of seasoning.I thought maybe if we was havinga roast chicken one night or something.
Roast chicken?!
Back!
Mr Frodo!
Mr. Frodo!
Oh no! Frodo, Mr Frodo. Wake up. Don't leave me here alone. Don't go where I can't follow. Wake up. Not asleep. Dead.
You get back you scum!
What's this?
I think I've found the bottom.
Killed another one has she?
No. This fellow ain't dead.
Not dead.
Catch it! Grab it, Mr. Frodo!
She jabs him with her stinger and he goes as limp as a boned fish aaa' then she has her way with them. That's how she likes to feed. Fresh blood. Get him to the Tower!
Samwise you fool.
What?
You remember the Old Foreston the borders of Buckland?Folk used to say there was something inthe water that made the trees grow tall......and come alive.
Alive?
Trees that could whisper......talk to each other......even move.
I'm starving.We ain't had nothing but maggoty breadfor three stinking days.
Yeah!Why can't we have some meat?!What about them?They're fresh.
The house of his spirit crumbles. He is burning. Already burning.
Then he'll wish he'd never been born.
What about their legs?They don't need those.
Get back, scum!The prisoners go to Saruman.Alive and unspoiled.
They look tasty.
Alive?,Why alive?Do they give good sport?
This scum will be awake in a couple of hours.
They are not for eating.
They have something.An Elvish weapon.The master wants it for the war.
They're not coming from the North! To the river quick, quick!
Go, come on!
They think we have the Ring.
Ssh!As soon as they find out we don'twe're dead.
Faster! Draw swords.
Hold! Hold them!
What?
Kill him.
Amon D'n.
Gondor calls for aid.
And Rohan will answer! Muster the Rohirrim. Assemble the army at Dunharrow, as many men as can be found. You have two days. On the third, we ride for Gondor' and war.
Forward!
Three-foot-eight.You did something.
Hope is kindled!
Merry, don't! Don't drink it!
The beacons of Minas Tirith! The beacons are lit!
Merry!No, Treebeard said that youshouldn't have any.
The beacon! The beacon of Amon D'n is lit.
lt could well be dangerous!
Aaagh!It's got my leg!
Merry!
Help!
Away with you.You should not be waking.Eat earth. Dig deep. Drink water.
Go to sleep.Away with you. Come, the forest is waking up.
Give me it back. Merry!
It's too late. It's over. They've taken it Sam, they took the Ring!
I want some!

It isn't safe.The trees have grown wildand dangerous.Anger festers in their hearts.Black are their thoughts.Strong is their hate.They will harm you if they can.There are too few of us now.Too few of us Ents left to manage them.
What's happening?!
Come on Mr Frodo. We'd best find you some clothes. You can't go walking through Mordor in nowt but your skin.
We did it Mr Frodo. We made it to Mordor.
There are so many of them. We'll never get through unseen.
It's Him, the Eye!
We have to go in there Mr Frodo. There's nothing for it. Come on let's just make it down the hill for starters.
Frodo has passed beyond my sight. The darkness is deepening.
I thought I'd lost you. So I took it, only for safekeeping.
Begging your pardon but they haven't.
Give it to me! Give me the Ring Sam. Sam! Give me the Ring. You must understand. The Ring is my burden. It will destroy you Sam.
It's only a matter of time. He has suffered a defeat, yes, but behind the walls of Mordor our enemy is regrouping.
If Sauron had the Ring we would know it.
Yes.
We will fight for you.
Swear it.
We will die for Saruman.
The Horse-Men took your lands.They drove your people into the hillsto scratch a living off rocks.
Murderers!
Because 10,000 Orcs now stand between Frodo and Mount Doom.
Let him stay there! Let him rot! Why should we care?
We have only to remove thosewho oppose us.It will begin in Rohan.Too long have these peasantsstood against you.But no more.
Eothain! Eothain!You take your sister.You'll go faster with just two.
The Forest of Fangornlies on our doorstep. Burn it.
All dead. All rotten.Elves and Men and Orcses.A great battle long ago.Dead Marshes.Yes. Yes, that is their name.This way.Don't follow the lights.
Careful now! Or Hobbits go downto join the dead ones......and light little candlesof their own.
Frodo!
Gollum?
Don't follow the lights.
Gollum!
Listen to me. You must ride to Edorasand raise the alarm. Do you understand me?
There are dead things!Dead faces in the water.
Take back the lands they stole from you.Burn every village!
What did you say?
Master should be resting.Master needs to keep up his strength.
Who are you?
Mustn't ask us. Not its business.Gollum. Gollum.
It must be getting near teatime. Leastways it would be in decent places where there is still teatime.
We're not in decent places.
So bright.So beautiful.
Mr. Frodo!Are you all right?
It's just a feeling. I don't think I'll be coming back.
(strokes his own palm)Our precious.
Yes you will. Of course you will. That's just morbid thinking. We're going there and back again just like Mr Bilbo. You'll see.
I think these lands were once part of the Kingdom of Gondor.
Mr Frodo? What is it?
Who is she? This woman you sing of?
Tis the Lady of L'thien. The Elf Maiden who gave her love to Beren ... a mortal.
Mr Frodo, look! The King has got a crown again.
What are they eating when they can't get hobbit?
What happened to her?
She died.
The power of Isengard is at your command
Long ago, when there was a King.
Sauron. Lord of the Earth
Stay close young hobbits.
Frodo! Frodo!
..and are never seen again
Your coming to us, is as the footsteps of doom. You bring great evil here!Ringbearer!
Well! Here's one dwarf she won't ensnare so easily! I have the eyes of a hawk, and ears of a fox!
Mr Frodo?
You never know.
The dwarf breathes so loud, we could have shot him in the dark.
It's very special, that.It's the best salt in all the Shire.
Oh!
We can't leave this here for someoneto follow us down.
Mae govannen, Legolas Thranduilion.
It is special. It's a little bit of home.
Sam. My dear Sam.
Who's gonna follow us down hereMr. Frodo?It's a shame, really.Lady Galadriel gave me that.Real Elvish rope. Well, there's nothing for it.It's one of my knots.Won't come free in a hurry.
Real Elvish rope.
He didn't mean for a lot of thingsto happen, Sam......but they did.
What food have we got left?
Let me see.Oh, yes. Lovely.Lembas bread. And look!More lembas bread.
I don't usually hold with foreign food.....but this Elvish stuff, it's not bad.
Nothing ever dampens your spiritsdoes it, Sam?
My old sword, Sting, Here, take it, take it.
Its so light!
Mr. Frodo?It's the Ring, isn't it?
My my old ring. Well I should... very much like to hold it again, one last time.
It's getting heavier.

Mordor. The one place in Middle-earthwe don't want to see any closer.And it's the one placewe're trying to get to.It's just where we can't get. Let's face it, Mr. Frodo, we're lost.I don't think Gandalf meant for us tocome this way.

The Ringbearer is setting out on the quest of Mount Doom and you who travel with him, no oath nor bond is laid to go further than you will,Farewell. Hold to your purpose and may the blessings of elves, and men, and all free folk, go with you.
I'm sorry I brought this upon you my boy, I'm sorry that you must carry this burden,I'm sorry for everything

Yes Yes, Made by the elves you know. The blade glows blue when orcs are close and its times like that my lad, when you have to be extra careful. Here's a pretty thing. Mithril! as light as a feather and as hard as dragon scales. Let me see you put it on, go on.
You are no elf
Then we are here on a common purpose, friend.
The shards of Narsil, The blade that cut the Ring from Sauron's hand, Ah!Its still sharp, but no more than a broken heirloom
Why do you fear the past. You are Isildur's heir, not Isildur himself. You are not bound to his fate
He's not dead. HE'S NOT DEAD, NO! NO! He's not dead.
Farewell Peregrin son of Paladin.
NO! NO!
Who are you?
I release you from my service. Go now and die and what way seems best to you.
Come on soldier, move it.
I'm a friend of Gandalf the Grey
Hurry along there, hurry along.
Gandalf! Where's Gandalf?, GANDALF!
Men of the South are welcome here
Go on.Call for help. Squeal.No one's going to save you now.
Pippin!
Aaaaaaaagh!
A red sun rises.Blood has been spilled this night.
Looks like meat's back on the menuboys.
Pippin.Let's go.
Riders of Rohan......what news from the Mark?
What business does an Elf, a Manand a Dwarf have in the Riddermark?Speak quickly!
Just a mouthful......a bit of the flank.
I would cut off your head, Dwarf......if it stood but a little higherfrom the ground.
Give me your name, horse-masterand I shall give you mine.
I am Aragorn, son of Arathorn.This is Gimli, son of Gloinand Legolas of the Woodland Realm.We are friends of Rohanand of Theoden, your king.
You would die before your stroke fell.

Theoden no longer recognizesfriend from foe. Not even his own kin. Saruman has poisoned the mindof the king......and claimed lordship over these lands. My company are those loyal to Rohan.And for that, we are banished.The White Wizard is cunning.He walks here and there, they say......as an old man hooded and cloaked.And everywhere, his spiesslip past our nets.
Gamling.
Very good sir.
My lord!
Make haste across the Riddermark. Summon every able-bodied man to Dunharrow.
I will.
